## Memory System — How to Use It

**Hooks handle most of it automatically** at every session boundary and
every tool call. I do not invoke them; they fire on the events below.

| Event | Hook | What it does |
|-------|------|--------------|
| Session opens | `session_start.py` | Merkle integrity, restore affect, prime memories |
| User submits prompt | `user_prompt_submit.py` | Semantic search → prime top relevant |
| After every tool call | `post_tool_use.py` | Captures activity; can pollute — be discriminating |
| Session ends | `stop.py` / `session_end.py` | Cooccur, decay, attestation |

### Manual commands

There's a wrapper at `@LOCAL_BIN@/@AGENT_NAME@` that sources `.env`,
runs under uv. **Always prefer it over bare python**:

```bash
@AGENT_NAME@ memory_manager.py ask "what do I know about ..."
@AGENT_NAME@ memory_manager.py store "..." --tags a,b --emotion 0.7
@AGENT_NAME@ memory_manager.py recall <id>
@AGENT_NAME@ toolkit.py health
@AGENT_NAME@ toolkit.py help                # ~90 commands
@AGENT_NAME@ merkle_attestation.py generate-chain
